"M01-P5605-X20" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :This device appears to be 2x3:2.
The WiSoC is both [[Celeno]] and [[Ralink]] branded (CL1820 - RT3662).
Per [ftp://ftp2.zyxel.com/WAP5605/firmware/WAP5605_V1.00(AAAH.2)_ReleaseNote.pdf ZyXEL's firmware release notes], this chip seems to be at least :partially derived from the RT2860/newer [[Ralink]] architecture chip. :'''cedrv.ko''', '''rt2860v2_ap.ko''', and '''rt2860v2_sta.ko''' appear to be :the wireless modules used.
"163QG-HCE6" may be the last characters of the '''Samsung''' RAM P/N.. :which would identify as a probable K4T51163QG-HCE6 (64MB).
*[http://www.celeno.com/press/showPR.aspx?pr_20110105 ''Celeno's True Video-Grade Wi-Fi Chipset is Selected'' by '''ZyXEL'''] *[http://www.speedguide.net/routers/zyxel-wap5605-5ghz-wireless-n-media-streaming-box-2349 ''ZyXEL WAP5605'' on '''SpeedGuide''']
The IP address varies upon the mode of the unit. *AP Mode: 192.168.1.2 *Client Mode: 192.168.1.10
